OL,3,CSwansea's big fly-tipping problem
OL,4,Cthat's getting worse
OL,6,FCllr Cyril Anderson, Swansea Council's
OL,7,Fcabinet member for community, said:
OL,8,F"It's disappointing to see that a
OL,9,Fminority of residents are continuing
OL,10,Fto fly-tip household waste rather than
OL,11,Fdispose of it correctly.
OL,13,F"We are doing everything we can to
OL,14,Fdeal with incidents of fly-tipping
OL,15,Fthat are reported to us. This includes
OL,16,Fefforts to identify those responsible
OL,17,Fand take appropriate action.
OL,19,F"Fly-tipping comes at a cost to the
OL,20,Fcouncil and it is money we would
OL,21,Fprefer to invest elsewhere."
